File: Health minister Zweli Mkhize. JOHANNESBURG - Health Minister Zweli Mkhize says the number of COVID-19 cases is most likely to exceed 200 by Friday. On Thursday, 34 more cases were confirmed, pushing the national total to 150. As a result, strict restrictions on public gatherings have come into effect. READ: What should you do if you think you have COVID-19? Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula also announced a total ban on cruise ships entering South African harbours. This is a measure to contain the spread of the coronavirus. Worldwide, 213 thousand people have been infected with coronavirus, more than 8,000 have died, but over 84,000 have recovered. READ: Second COVID-19 case at UCT China has recorded no new locally transmitted cases of COVID-19. But, it has imported 34 cases, mainly from Spain and Britain. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.